Manchester City moved into second place in the Premier League, following a comfortable 3-1 win over Bournemouth on Sunday afternoon. The champions raced into a two-goal lead, thanks to Sergio Aguero and Raheem Sterling. The hosts pulled one back through Liverpool loanee Harry Wilson, but Aguero grabbed a second to secure maximum points for Pep Guardiola’s men. City now have seven points, two less than leaders Liverpool. The Reds beat Arsenal 3-1 at Anfield on Saturday, to maintain their perfect start to the campaign. The Gunners dropped down to third place as a result with six points, with Leicester City in fourth position. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.